div.div: Find email address for a domain using google?

Not perfect but occasionally this returns a gem Google Search for: (email | mailto | contact) * cnn.com You are asking for 'all pages on a domain' so in theory something like "site:cnn.com (email | mailto | contact) * cnn.com" may work
Excel automation, how to detect if user runs macro in excel worksheet or clicks 'Run Macro' CommandBarControl?

I do not know if there is 'an event' in the .NET automation but I know TrackToAct.com (full disclosure my co.) has a VBA code snippet or DLL that your drop into track events. It enables you to tag events and report on the usage via web dashboard.

Many ways to accomplish this but the one thaf comes to mind is to create the Transifex source plugin yourself. https://www.gatsbyjs.org/docs/create-source-plugin/#create-source-plugin Once nodes are created with that plugin consider using the node mapping feature. https://www.gatsbyjs.org/docs/gatsby-config/#mapping-node-types
